It's great having all 3 movies in one package. These movies are fun, and the cheerleading routines are great! Anyone who says cheerleading isn't a sport, is crazy! The tumbling, the constant movement, the tosses, the pyramids. It's not just standing on the sidelines at a game clapping any jumping up and down anymore, like it was years ago. These kids work. Hard. Ten times better than watching anything that glorifies teen pregnancy. Plus, I am also a big fan of Kirsten Dunst, Gabrielle Union, Solange Knowles, and Hayden Panetierre. Good stuff.
Love this movie can watch this all day

Every real cheerleader has seen at least the first one, and it is a classic. These movies put diversity in the cheerleader world and are a must see for any real cheerleader! Three different story lines but one things in common, bad ass cheerleaders. Good routines, great tumbling and puts pride in the true athlete.

This purchase went perfectly. The shipping was excellent and the product arrived timely and without any damage. The movies are exactly as described and to be honest were better than we expected. This is my daughters favorite movie and I had not even heard of the sequels so I was so glad!

Although some of the gestures are somewhat inappropriate at some times, I think these are ok. Heck, my girls have already been subject to more info in school because they've both had sex education classes already. I approve these movies.

This is a must have for all cheerleaders and a great party movie.  Snarky, a little action, and they're all in one box.

I purchased this 3-movie pack directly from Amazon and they expedited the shipping so I could give it as a gift a few days later.  I really appreciated talking to Bob at Amazon who answered my questions and helped get this product to me the next day.

I am purchasing movies that star Philip Winchester.  I am looking for a movie entitled "The Heart of the Earth" that was made in 2007.  If this seller can find this dvd that would play in the US in English, I would purchase it from him.  eBay has one for sale from Turkey and one from Australia, both of which will not play in the US.
The first two movies are definitely the ones to watch.  If you have children, then the third one will entertain them.  Overall, I liked them one without complaint.

Cute movies. My daughter started cheerleading this past year and wanted to see the first movie. For Christmas we got her this series. She's a tween now so they are perfect. And she doesn't act like any of the characters!!
These movies are fun to watch with friends! They're great for when you want to have a girls movie night.
My daughter received this as a Xmas gift and loves all the cheerleader movies, so to get all of them at one price was great
I love the cheer movies. Bring It On series is fantastic. They may be more for the teen crowd but I really enjoy them.

We have a 21 yr. old daughter and a 11.5 yr. old daughter and trying to find a movie for all of us to watch together can be challenging at times. We laughed and had fun together! Our 21 yr. old laughed and smiled and rolled her eyes some but our 11.5 yr. old loved it and wanted to do the cheers and dances in our home,only. A little bit of the language and additude pushed the limits I allow in our lives and home but these movies(Bring It On: Cheertastic 3-Movie Pack)allowed us to have a fun night together! Our 11.5 yr. old had friends over for a sleepover and they had a blast with these movies and popcorn! I don't know how many times they have been played now. I would reccomend this to a parent of a middleschooler or older and especially if the like cheerleading! They are cute,fun,and a value for the cost!

This is a cute classic my daughter used to love watching together so I got it for my 2 grandaughters. They are 5 and 10 year old cheerleaders. I still favor the original with Kirsten dunst and gabrielle union, but they like the 2nd and 3rd one. Was fun watching them try to learn the routines at home.
I love this movie but it wasn't as interesting as the first two movies I would probably pass this one on to one of my grand daughters as a gift for them .
